news.title: China to cut existing mortgage rates by October-end to boost property market
news.para: Commercial banks should, in batches, reduce interest rates on existing mortgages to no less than 30 basis points (bps) below the Loan Prime Rate (LPR), the central bank's benchmark rate for mortgages, according to a statement released by the People's Bank of China (PBOC).

news.title: Chennai civic body empanels trucks for clearing construction debris
news.para: The city generates about 850 tonnes of construction waste daily, with illegal dumping rampant. On Saturday, the corporation fined multiple households and trucks of 2.05 lakh for dumping waste in areas — Kodungaiyur, Captain Cotton, and Vyasarpadi canals.

news.title: Delhi development body enhances housing schemes with a fresh finish and green spaces
news.para: "DDA's horticulture department is busy developing greens around the housing pockets to improve the quality of life for buyers. Besides, additional final touches are being given to housing blocks to add value," said an official.

news.title: Indore administration receives 2,444 applications seeking land ownership rights
news.para: The district administration organised camps at tehsil offices in Indore for granting leases, in which around 266 applications were received in Kanadia, 334 in Rau, 687 in Malharganj, 595 in Juni Indore, and 562 in Bhicholi Hapsi.

news.title: Maharashtra CM assures to make Cidco houses freehold in Nashik
news.para: Shinde's assurances came while he was addressing a gathering at a local programme for the Balasaheb Thackeray Smriti Udyan in the Gangapur Road area on Saturday.

news.title: Uttarakhand HC quashes lease cancellation order issued to housing project in SIIDCUL Haridwar
news.para: The petitioner, Delhi Apartments Pvt Ltd (DAPL), was allocated five plots on lease in State Infrastructure & Industrial Development Corporation of Uttarakhand Ltd (SIIDCUL) DAPL has started construction on four plots, while the project on the fifth plot has not yet commenced, the lease of which has been revoked.

news.title: Lavasa creditors set eligibility floor to begin resolution 2.0
news.para: The minutes of the meeting of the committee of creditors (CoC) held on September 17 show that 77% of lenders led by Union Bank of India (UBI) have agreed to a minimum criteria for bidders which is a change from the last time the process ran without any eligible criteria to "maximise participation" of applicants.

news.title: Supertech opposes NBCC’s takeover plan to complete 14,000 flats
news.para: The realtor also criticised NBCC's cost estimate to complete the projects, which is nearly double that of Supertech's. The developer suggested that stakeholders would benefit more if it was allowed to construct one project at a time, like that in the case of Doon Square.

news.title: Yamuna Expressway authority mandates stamp duty for builder-buyer agreements
news.para: This requirement, already outlined in UP-Rera rules, ensures that buyers have valid proof of their flat registration and corresponding stamp duty payment at the time of booking. This will protect homebuyers from potential complications related to the sale or purchase of flats and plots from developers, officials said.

news.title: Mumbai police arrest man for cheating buyers of Rs 100 crore
news.para: An officer of BKC police station said, "Jawale deceived people by enticing them with the prospect of acquiring residential or commercial property at prices below market value. He would gain confidence of potential buyers by presenting them with flats seized by banks from loan defaulters and were purportedly available for auction.

news.title: Decision on scrapping NA tax for housing societies in urban areas likely before Maharashtra polls
news.para: The tax is applicable for societies that do not come under gaothan areas in the municipal corporation or council areas.

news.title: Ulhasnagar civic body collects over Rs 5 crore property tax on September 28
news.para: Jamir Lengrekar, Additional Municipal Commissioner of UMC, said, "On this special day, any property tax holder who paid his property tax dues in one day was given 100 percent concession in all late fees."

news.title: North Goa police verifies credentials of 40,000 tenants
news.para: Superintendent of police (SP) North Goa, Akshat Kaushal, said that the drive was launched in all police stations of North Goa and special camps were set up in major market areas.

news.title: Chennai: Tambaram and Avadi corporations to expand from January 2025
news.para: The Tambaram Corporation will incorporate 18 villages, including Agaramthen, Medavakkam, Kovilambakkam, Cowl Bazaar, Mudichur, Perumbakkam, Nanmangalam, Pozhichalur, Tirusulam, Ottiyambakkam, Thiruvanchery, Vengaivasal, Madurapakkam, Moovarasampattu, and Sithalapakkam.

news.title: Hyderabad: Not demolishing structures permitted by civic bodies, says HYDRAA chief
news.para: HYDRAA commissioner AV Ranganath said they demolished structures which were unauthorised, permissions cancelled and unoccupied. He clarified that HYDRAA is not silent on rich and influential people, but doing some groundwork, which takes some time.

news.title: Mumbai: MMRDA approves Rs 8,498 crore slum rehabilitation scheme in Ghatkopar East
news.para: The Maharashtra govt had earlier authorised the Slum Rehabilitation Authority (SRA) to carry out such projects in collaboration with local self-governing bodies and agencies like MMRDA, MHADA, CIDCO, and others.

news.title: Mumbai: First batch of BDD chawl residents to get new flats in January 2025
news.para: “Around 550 flats are nearing completion. We had promised to hand them over to residents by March 2025 but we are confident we can do so by January,” said a senior Maharashtra Housing Area Development Authority (MHADA) official requesting anonymity.

news.title: Prayagraj development body reduces prices of unsold flats by 10%
news.para: 256 flats of PDA have not been sold for a long time. These flats are in Kalindipuram and Naini. PDA has sought applications several times for allotment.

news.title: Rules for Tamil Nadu apartment ownership act rolled out
news.para: As per the rules, apartment owners must establish an association, create by e-laws and register the association, with at least four apartment owners required to form an association.

news.title: Pidilite invests Rs 5 crore in home improvement & maintenance platform Wify
news.para: This pre-series A funding round was led by Capria and Mount Judi Ventures, with participation from Blume Ventures.
